OL,3,CMother put 'own child at risk' after
OL,4,Ctaking them to protest
OL,6,FA woman has been convicted of throwing
OL,7,Fliquid at a police officer during
OL,8,Fprotests outside of a hotel housing
OL,9,Fasylum seekers - while her child was
OL,10,Fin a pushchair next to her.
OL,12,FNevey Smith, 21, cried in the dock as
OL,13,Fshe admitted violent disorder during a
OL,14,Fdisturbance outside a hotel in Newton
OL,15,FHeath, Manchester, on 31 July.
OL,17,FManchester Magistrates Court heard
OL,18,FSmith was taking her child to her
OL,19,Fgrandmother's when she saw a family
OL,20,Fmember outside the hotel.
